FORMER Eskom Board Chairman Jabu Mabuza has due to covid-19 complications on Wednesday. His death comes as the country is dealing with the third wave of covid-19 infections. Condolences are pouring for the former chair of Eskom on social media. Mabuza resigned over load shedding early last. This was after the Deputy President said the Eskom Board misled President Cyril Ramaphosa on load shedding. Absolutely shocked at the passing of #jabumabuza Interviewed him a few years back, was a very nice guy. Another #COVID19 statistic pic.twitter.com/nb07BNIEGM 